<strong>GREAT NEWS: THE WINTER PARK WEEKEND SKI TRAIN IS BACK!</strong><br />
<br />
The <strong>Amtrack Winter Park Express Ski Train</strong> weekend service from Denver to Winter Park will be running Jan 07 - Mar 26, 2017.<br />
Buy a round trip or 1 way ticket for as low as $39 each way.&nbsp; You can stay overnight or stay for a week.<br />
<br />
The round-trips will run on Saturdays and Sundays, with an additional round-trip on Martin Luther King Day and Presidents Day. Winter Park Express trains will enable customers to skip the congestion and stop-and-go ski traffic on I-70 and U.S. 40 while enjoying a comfortable and scenic two hour ride on the historic route through Moffat Tunnel.<br />
<br />
The weekend morning train departs Union Station in downtown Denver at 7:00am and arrives at Winter Park Resort platform at approximately 9:00am.<br />
The weekend afternoon train will depart Winter Park at 4:30pm and arrive at Denver&#39;s Union Staion at approximately 6:40pm.<br />
<br />
Reservations must be made and tickets purchased by 11:59 p.m. Mountain Time the day before departure.<br />
Two children ages 2-12 can ride for half-fare with each ticketed adult.<br />
Passengers with disabilities may book by calling 800-USA-RAIL.<br />
<br />
A new commuter rail line from Denver International Airport to Union Station enables visitors from throughout the country and across the globe to travel from their flight to Winter Park. Seamless rail connectivity will be available from the airport, to the Winter Park Express and on to Winter Park Resort, without having to rent a car, secure a shuttle or navigate mountain roads.&nbsp;<br />
